## D016: Typography — Fira Code as Primary Typeface
**Date**: 2026-03-02
**Status**: DECIDED

**Observation**: kashifshah.net uses Fira Code (monospace) for all text — body, headings,
and code. The site uses self-hosted woff2 files with weights 300-700 plus a variable font.
The aesthetic: terminal/hacker feel, unified typeface across the entire site, dense but
readable with ligatures enabled.

The current unratified.org type stack:
- Body: Charter (serif) — print-editorial feel
- Heading: Inter (sans-serif) — clean modern feel
- Mono: JetBrains Mono / Fira Code — code only

**Decision**: Adopt Fira Code as the unified typeface for all text (body, heading, mono).
Load via Google Fonts (weights 300-700) with preconnect for performance. Enable ligatures
and contextual alternates. Base font-size 16px, line-height 1.6.

**Reasoning**:
- Primary audience (Hackers, HN community) responds naturally to monospace aesthetics
- Signals intellectual honesty and technical precision — consistent with fair witness framing
- Unified typeface simplifies the design system and reduces cognitive load
- Fira Code's ligature support (→, !=, etc.) renders well in data-forward content
- kashifshah.net demonstrates this aesthetic at production quality
- Simpler than self-hosting: Google Fonts CDN with preconnect provides adequate performance

**What follows**:
- --font-body, --font-heading, --font-mono all map to Fira Code
- Future style adaptation from kashifshah.net: color palette (dark terminal theme),
  spacing system, layout proportions
- D017 captures the five-lens audience expansion

